                  "system": "http://loinc.org",
                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding our mutual patient, a 90-year-old female who was admitted on 17/01/1959 at her own voluntary request for surgical sterilization. Prior to the procedure, a thorough pre-operative assessment was conducted, including clinical examination and routine laboratory investigations, confirming her fitness for surgery despite her advanced age. The patient provided informed consent, confirming her autonomous decision for permanent contraception. Surgical sterilization was performed on 17/01/1959 via tubal ligation under general anaesthesia without intraoperative or postoperative complications. Post-operative recovery was uneventful. The patient was discharged home on 18/01/1959 in good general condition. No further gynaecological follow-up is deemed necessary unless clinically indicated. Please do not hesitate to contact me should you require any further information. Yours sincerely, Dr. [Treating Physician]</div>"
            },
            "code": {
